The paper focuses on information retrieval in data visualization, which is a common topic in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of $\alpha$-divergence for optimization suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category, while the focus on precision and recall in visualization suggests a computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The statistical framework and distribution used in the paper suggest a statistics (cs.ST) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of nonlinear dimensionality reduction suggests a data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
